groups?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Wandor, while our soloing is superior to many, it still has limitations.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is true, but we don't have as many limitations as other soloing classes. The no summon thing is pretty universal in PoP since everything hits too hard to go toe to toe with. The snare/root is personal preference, keep in mind that enchanters and mages never get the snare option and root is useless since it breaks too easy with damage.<br>
<br>
The available is the single biggest limitation that we have, but this is also where we compared to other classes. While the PoK books has made travel easier on other classes, we can still gate to more places and faster. Most gaters bind in PoK for easy book access, whereas we can bind in PoT for easy planar access, if we need books, we just port there instead. We can use this to our advantage since it is easy for us to check many different solo camps rather quickly.<br>
<br>
My suggestion for anyone not in the elemental planes is to use your imagination when looking for solo spots. There are many that people either ignore or it just doesn't occur to them. Here are a few that I have found are rarely taken:<br>
<br>
1. HoH entrance - most people head for the basement when they want to solo. Even when all of the basement camps are taken, the entrance mobs are almost always up. The initial pull is a little tricky since you have to find a way to get 2 inside mobs to kite with the 2 entrance mobs, but its really not that hard to figure out. Normally I don't recommend kiting neat a GY, but this is an exception. The GY area is perfect for kiting and big enough that  you can avoid anyone who happens to die and wants to sit there.<br>
<br>
2. Butterflies in PoN - If you can make the run to PoNb without agroing anything (easy during prime time) then you can solo butterflies pretty easily. They are level 60 if memory serves me so they are still good experience and they are rarely camped even on a busy night.<br>
<br>
3. PoV undead - I don't think I have ever seen this camp taken. There are at least 2 camps of snareable skeles on the forest side of PoV. They are all level 59 so they are good for 24% per quad.<br>
<br>
4. BoT - the bees are snareable and they don't summon. You can run all the way up with invis if you know the way. This place is also out of the way enough that it is rarely camped, and even if it is camped, there are enough mobs and a big enough area to support several groups/soloers.<br>
<br>
There are similar spots all over the place, you just have to go out and find them. I would also disagree than pet classes have more options because we can can do any camp they can if there is enough room to get out of melee range long enough to root. The few places that are too small or have too many mobs to do this is balanced by the spots where the mobs hit way too hard for a pet to tank. These camps can still be done by pet classes but they have to agro kite, which takes considerable longer, particularly for classes that can't snare since most classes don't have fast enough casting nukes to pull it off.<br>
<br>
I stand by my original statement, a well played wizard is the uncontested king of solo exp. While it might be possible for a charm killer to exceed our exp per hour on occassion, I don't think it can be done consistently since the charm nerf. Death is much more common with charm not being as reliable and that severly cuts down on the exp per hour gained when you have to CR a time or 2 a night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Warriors ph34r me!<BR>Gnomercy for Gno-one!</span><br>  Posts: 2076<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 6:18 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are wizards balanced in EXP-groups?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and I agree with Wandor that wizard soloing capabilities are probably the best in game right now, given the right gear.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I would qualify that statement with some more detail. Rather than say our soloing capabilities are tied to our gear, I would say that we solo more effectively than other classes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>with a similar level of gear.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> All things being equal - gear, AAs, knowledge of class, etc. - a wizard can out solo any other class.<br>
<br>
Sure, a wizard with 3k mana and no FT with 6aa doesn't have anywhere near the soloing abilities of a wizard with 6k mana, 15ft, and 250aa. But, that wizard will solo better than another class with similar equipment and aa. Our spells are simply better suited for soloing than any other classes. We can always do damage because we have a wider variety of damage types to choose from and in a pinch we can use lures. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aauminki>Aauminki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/03 6:07 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are wizards balanced in EXP-groups?</span><hr size=1> You miss my point, Wandor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
